author: stsp
msg: Start teaching 'svn patch' about git-style 'rename' information.
'svn patch' now moves a patch target which has the following
extra information as generated by 'git diff --find-renames':
rename from OLD_PATH
rename to NEW_PATH
Note that 'svn diff --git' does not create such diff headers yet.
Rename information was already parsed by the diff parser but the
patch code didn't make use of it so far.
* subversion/libsvn_client/patch.c
(patch_target_t): Add 'move_target_abspath'.
(choose_target_filename): Return the old name in case of rename.
(init_patch_target): If the diff contains a move operation, sanitize
and store the move destination path in target->move_target_abspath.
(send_patch_notification): Send 'A' and 'D' notifications for moves.
(install_patched_target): In case the patch target is moved, write the
patched contents directly to the move destination path, perform
a meta-data-only move from the target's old location, and delete the
old location from disk. This part of the implementation needs further
work, e.g. we don't check for unversioned obstructions at the move
destination yet!
(apply_patches): Run install_patched_target() in case of a move.
* subversion/tests/cmdline/patch_tests.py
(patch_git_rename, test_list): New test.
